HDAC1/2 knockdown significantly reverses cisplatin resistance and tumorsphere formation
('HDAC1/2 knockdown', 'reverses', 'cisplatin resistance tumorsphere formation')

To further understand the role of HDACs in chemoresistance and stem cell function, we knocked down HDAC1 and HDAC2 in cisplatin resistant cell lines (Fig. ). HDAC1&amp;2 knockdown significantly reversed resistance in cisplatin-resistant CAL27-CisR cells (Fig. ). Similarly, HDAC1&amp;2 knockdown significantly decreased tumorsphere formation in cisplatin-resistant cell lines (Fig. ). We have recently shown that survivin is one of the key molecules that regulate cisplatin resistance [].

We next examined if HDAC1&amp;2 knockdown reverses cisplatin resistance by downregulating survivin expression.

Indeed, HDAC1&amp;2 knockdown markedly decreased survivin levels in CAL27-CisR and UD-SCC-2-CisR cells (Fig. ). In addition, HDAC1&amp;2 knockdown also markedly downregulated nanog expression (Fig. ).
